 with that balancing system I am not seeing?<br><br><br>(And if Mythic wanted to get extreme against exploits of this system, it'd have to make it so you couldn't log in the frontier.  No biggie.)<br><br>Scorn Hull<br>Retired AGM of Reckoning, Guinevere <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ueregil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eregil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.libero.it/okandrea/Eregil.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/16/02 3:21:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=233.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.libero.it/okandrea/ereliz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poll on &quot;Whether PvE Bonuses Fix a PvP Problem:&quo</span><hr size=1> This is not an easy question as it has a LOT implications:<br><br>1) How you exactly determine &quot;underdog&quot;?<br>Do you count the realm population on that server, do you count lvl40+ population, do you RP's earned in the week, do you count the number of relics, etc.<br><br>2) What exactly does faster exp mean?<br>100% faster or 5% faster?<br><br>3) When is this change coming in?<br>Will it take the time it has taken housing, spell crafting, respec and so on?<br><br>4) Will this get NEW people to play in the underdog realm or will twinks have a field day?<br><br>There are a lot of issues here and none are easy to determine, I would much favour a system that gave a PvP advantage to the underdog realm rather than an exp one.<br><br>But at least Mythic has seen the problem and trying to do something about it but the problem is WHEN will this happen... in a few months time when all have left? <p><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="http://users.libero.it/okandrea/EreNi.gif"></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvivaxkithicor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vivax Kithicor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/16/02 10:36:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=233.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poll on &quot;Whether PvE Bonuses Fix a PvP Problem:&quo</span><hr size=1> My suggestion was to define &quot;underdog&quot; as measured by population in the particular frontier.<br>Why not take levels into account?  Because Mythic is removing the level-based modifiers for offense and defense in PvP.<br><br>Why only use frontier population numbers and only modify frontier fighting abilities?<br>Because if Albion has 1,800 on, and Midgard has 600 on, I don't think that should affect Midgard's chances at defeating its dragon.<br><br>Sure, using my suggestion, if there are 800 Albions in Emain, 400 Hibernians in Emain, and 8 Midgardians in Emain, then those are 8 lucky Midgardians.  Hell, I'd consider reactivating my 2 level 50 accounts for that.<br><br>OH!  I just caught the irony here:  Mythic on one hand gives &quot;underdog&quot; realms exp bonuses, while on the other removes level-based PvP advantages.  ROFL!<br><br>Scorn Hull <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=233.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=233.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td v